 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=klumhru>Klumhru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 1:02:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grouping specs</span><hr size=1> I now have some 240 spectre kills to my name, and I'd like to share some points. I'm 48 now and plan to try to use these guys to 51 (Column of Frost, Wyvern time), but I've seen some trying to use the tactic I used originally. At first I tried pulling them down to the shore and then kiting them along the shore line. I did find out though that I often had them in awkward positions, either high above me, or far below. So I decided to experiment with pulling them along on top of the Island, and have found that this works much better. There are several points that jut out from the &quot;hat&quot; of the Island, so to speak, and allow you a long view over a relatively flat area. I found that running between these points counterclockwise allowed me to get to each point exactly when CoF popped, nuke, run to next, etc. I've even started referring to these points as nuking stations :-) Lev and SoW/JBoots required of course.<br>
Also some stats:<br>
11 minutes per quad (approx at L47, can range from 10-12)<br>
3 quads per SoW potion charge<br>
1 - 1.2 blue bub of xp per quad<br>
1 yellow per hour<br>
1 Level per 5 hours<br>
UNFAIR! :-D <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=91376"><img src="http://www.snigel.org/klumhru/klumhru.jpg" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uscylth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scylth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 4:12:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grouping specs</span><hr size=1>      It seems to me that on some of these posts people sometimes forget exactly which mobs started greening at what level, and how much exp a quad was giving at each level.  I can't remember the specifics of earlier levels myself.  Since I have just finished the spectres and so that no 48 or 49 wizard goes off there to level, I would like to say that the spectres are great from 45 - 47, as good exp as you will find.  At 47 they begin to green out (about 50 -50) but the exp is still ok.  At 48 they are definately not worth quadding.  Most are green at that point.  My last 5 quads there at 48 gave me a little more than one blue.  I can get more exp doing single spirocs for the same amount of time, and I suppose the same holds true for wyverns in CS. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhekken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hekken</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/31/01 12:39:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grouping specs</span><hr size=1> The specs are in level range 33 to 37.  They have about 1700 hp.  They are somewhat spell casters, but the only spell I have seen them cast is a low level lifetap much like the 44+ necro pets.  They do also stun as part of their melee attack.<br>
<br>
I started doing them at level 40, but had to upgrade my equipment to 200 int and 200 mana (plus Harvest) to succeed.  In addition, I had my level 49 druid present for buffs (Sprit of Wolf, anyone?) and safety.  This allowed me to actually get the experience for the kills even if I normally would have had to abort the kite and get out of there.<br>
<br>
Starting at level 44, the lowest level spectres will no longer assist their higher level brothers, and will need to be pulled &quot;manually&quot;.  I solve this by fluxing one, running a little bit and turning around to see if they are all present.  If not, I take one extra round fluxing the latecomers, run around their spawn point a couple of times and then snare the pack.<br>
<br>
 <p>Nadena, lvl 42 High Elf Enchanter<br>
Hekken, lvl 49 Halfling Druid<br>
